<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 11 at 8:24AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow to continue through the morning hours...
Light snow will continue over the southern high plains and much
of Cascade County through the morning hours. Snowfall amounts will
mostly be around an inch or less, but below freezing road
surfaces have resulted in slippery spots developing on area
roadways. The worst condtions will be along highway 200 from
Lincoln to Great Falls and along highway 287 near Augusta.
Anyone traveling should allow extra travel time, slow down, and
be prepared for a thin layer of snow and ice to be present on road
surfaces.</description>
